note: Several notes describing the manusript laid in at the front.

msContents.summary: Summary of the seven chapters of Apollonius' Conics with explanations and diagrams.

supportDesc.extent: iii, 39, iv leaves : 318 x 208 (240 x 140) mm, bound to 328 x 213 x 13 mm

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed.

decoNote: Numerous geometric diagrams in black ink.

binding.p: Bound in orange cardboard with leather half covers; plain paper doublure.

origin.p: Copy completed on 16 Jumādá al-Ūlá 1283 A.H. (1866) (f. 39v).

provenance: Formerly owned by George Arthur Plimpton (bookplate inside front and back covers).
